Nouns (core)
mogri			noun; the root concept; may be used as countable or uncountable depending on context
mogris			noun; plural of mogri when discrete instances are intended

Verbs (core actions)
mogrify			verb; to cause something to become mogri; to impart mogri
mogrifies		verb; third-person singular present of mogrify
mogrified		verb; past tense / past participle of mogrify
mogrifying		verb; present participle / gerund of mogrify

demogrify		verb; to remove mogri; to reverse the effects of mogrification
demogrifies		verb; third-person singular present of demogrify
demogrified		verb; past tense / past participle of demogrify
demogrifying		verb; present participle / gerund of demogrify

Event nouns (processes)
mogrification		noun; the process or act of mogrifying
mogrifications		noun; plural of mogrification (multiple instances or types)

demogrification		noun; the process or act of demogrifying
demogrifications	noun; plural of demogrification (multiple instances or types)

Adjectives (unprefixed)
mogric			adjective; having the quality of mogri; pertaining to mogri
mogrious		adjective; characterised by or full of mogri
mogriantic		adjective; relating to mogri in an active or agentive sense
mogricious		adjective; inclined toward or expressive of mogri
mogrificant		adjective; producing or effecting mogri

Adjectives (prefixed: un-)
unmogric		adjective; not mogric; lacking the quality of mogri
unmogrious		adjective; not characterised by mogri
unmogriantic		adjective; not agentively related to mogri
unmogricious		adjective; not inclined toward mogri
unmogrificant		adjective; not producing or effecting mogri

Adjectives (prefixed: dis-)
dismogric		adjective; disordered, broken, or absent in relation to mogri
dismogrious		adjective; characterised by loss or breakdown of mogri
dismogriantic		adjective; actively out of alignment with mogri
dismogricious		adjective; tending away from mogri
dismogrificant		adjective; disrupting or undoing mogri

Adjectives (prefixed: contra-)
contramogric		adjective; explicitly opposed to mogri
contramogrious		adjective; characterised by opposition to mogri
contramogriantic	adjective; agentively opposing mogri
contramogricious	adjective; inclined against mogri
contramogrificant	adjective; producing effects contrary to mogri
